<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Random Buildings with Windows</title>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <script src="https://aframe.io/releases/1.2.0/aframe.min.js"></script>
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            overflow: hidden;
            background-color: #000; /* Background color for the body */
        }
        a-scene {
            display: block; /* Ensure the scene takes whole viewport */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <a-scene>
        <!-- Green Floor -->
        <a-box position="0 0.05 0" width="100" height="0.1" depth="100" color="green"></a-box>

        <!-- Black Main Road -->
        <a-box position="0 0.05 0" width="5" height="0.1" depth="100" color="black"></a-box>

        <!-- Camera -->
        <a-camera position="0 5 20"></a-camera>

        <!-- Sky -->
        <a-sky color="#87CEEB"></a-sky>

        <!-- Buildings will be generated here -->
        <a-entity id="buildings"></a-entity>
    </a-scene>

    <script>
        function createBuilding() {
            const building = document.createElement('a-box');
            const randomWidth = Math.random() * 4 + 1; // Width between 1 and 5
            const randomDepth = Math.random() * 4 + 1; // Depth between 1 and 5
            const randomHeight = Math.random() * 10 + 3; // Height between 3 and 13
            const xPosition = Math.random() * 80 - 40; // Random X position
            const zPosition = Math.random() * 80 - 40; // Random Z position
            const randomColor = `hsl(${Math.random() * 360}, 100%, 50%)`; // Random color

            // Set building attributes
            building.setAttribute('color', randomColor);
            building.setAttribute('width', randomWidth);
            building.setAttribute('depth', randomDepth);
            building.setAttribute('height', randomHeight);
            building.setAttribute('position', `${xPosition} ${randomHeight / 2} ${zPosition}`);

            // Generate windows
            for (let i = 0; i < 30; i++) {
                const window = document.createElement('a-plane');
                const windowWidth = 0.2;
                const windowHeight = 0.3;
                const randomX = (Math.random() - 0.5) * (randomWidth); // Random position within building width
                const randomY = Math.random() * (randomHeight - windowHeight); // Random Y position within building height
                const randomZ = (Math.random() - 0.5) * (randomDepth); // Random position within building depth
                const windowColor = Math.random() < 0.5 ? 'white' : 'yellow'; // Randomly assign color

                window.setAttribute('color', windowColor);
                window.setAttribute('width', windowWidth);
                window.setAttribute('height', windowHeight);
                window.setAttribute('position', `${randomX} ${randomY} ${randomZ}`);
                window.setAttribute('rotation', '0 0 0');

                // Attach window to building
                building.appendChild(window);
            }

            // Add building to the scene
            document.getElementById('buildings').appendChild(building);
        }

        // Create 10 buildings
        for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
            createBuilding();
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
1. **Building Creation**: The `createBuilding` function creates a building as an `<a-box>` element with:
   - Random width, depth, and height.
   - A random color generated using HSL.
   - A random position for placement within the scene.

2. **Windows**: Each building has 30 `<a-plane>` elements as windows, which are:
   - Positioned randomly on the building's face.
   - Colored either white or yellow based on a random determination.

3. **Camera and Environment**: The scene includes:
   - A green floor and a black main road.
   - An upward-facing camera positioned to provide a good view of the buildings.

4. **Execution**: After defining the `createBuilding` function, a loop creates 10 buildings to populate the scene.

You can simply copy this code into an HTML file and open it in a web browser that supports A-Frame. You will see a vibrant scene with colorful buildings, each adorned with randomly colored windows. Enjoy!

